query.result:
46 "Do not be afraid," said my lord;
47 "be reassured, for we are at a good point;
48 do not clench, but relax all your strength.

49 You have now reached purgatory:
50 see there the cliff that encloses it all around;
51 see the entrance there where it seems disjoined.

52 A short while ago, at the dawn that precedes the day,
53 when your soul was sleeping within you,
54 a lady came over the flowers with which it is adorned down there

55 and said: "I am Lucia;
56 let me take this sleeping man;
57 I will make his path easier for him".

58 Sordello and the other noble spirits remained;
59 she took you, and when it was daylight,
60 she came up here; and I followed in her footsteps.

61 Here she put you down, but first
62 her beautiful eyes showed me that entrance open;
63 then she and sleep departed together."

